	</string>
	<string id="ui_mcm_spatial_audio_desc_preset">
		<text>Presets Settings - Reverb effect related settings, you can find default presets in script/sar_reverb_preset.script or make custom preset in the Preset Editor tab</text>
	</string>
	<string id="ui_mcm_spatial_audio_desc_dbug">
		<text>Dev shits</text>
	</string>


	<string id="ui_mcm_spatial_audio_desc_editor1">
		<text>Welcome to the Preset Editor, scroll down to see how to use</text>
	</string>
	<string id="ui_mcm_spatial_audio_desc_editor2">
		<text>1. Enable the editor, then load your custom preset (or any other preset as base)</text>
	</string>
	<string id="ui_mcm_spatial_audio_desc_editor3">
		<text>2. Start editing, edit the value, jump out to see the effect in action </text>
	</string>
	<string id="ui_mcm_spatial_audio_desc_editor4">
		<text>3. If you're done, scroll down, type in the name for custom preset (can overwrite existing preset), and press export. </text>
	</string>
	<string id="ui_mcm_spatial_audio_desc_editor5">
		<text>4. Bam! you can set the preset into the main setting in mcm. </text>
	</string>
	<string id="ui_mcm_spatial_audio_desc_editor6">
		<text>Documentation for all effect is in mod-folder/SAR-DOC/Effect Extension Guide.pdf</text>
	</string>
